p.01703376c4a81c0e9d91: Executes a function on each item of a list to create a unique "reduced" value from it.
p.01703376c4a81c0e9d92:
The reduce brick executes the user-provided function (reducer) on each item of the provided list, passing in the return value from the calculation on the preceding element.
The final result of running the reducer across all elements or the list is the single `result` output value of the brick.

An initial value can be provided to process the first element of the list.

## Example:
- inputs
  1. list = `[1, 2, 3]`
  2. reducer = `(sum, item) => sum + item`
  3. initial value = 0
- outputs
  1. result = 6
The original list to iterate on.
The function to execute for each item of the list which returns the next resulting value.
The return value after calling the reducer on all items of the list.
